    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change border color of mui alert in React js, you can use this css . It will change border color of mui alert in react‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change border color of mui alert in React js, you can use this css <code class=\"language-text\">border: \"10px solid blue\"</code>. It will change border color of mui alert in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How to change border color of mui alert in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui Alert in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code> </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI alert.</li>\n<li>Use the Alert Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI alert.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> createTheme<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ThemeProvider <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/styles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Alert <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Alert\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the Alert Component</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">Alert</code> component in your react js. For example, The Alert component is  used to display important messages or notifications to users. You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Alert></code> component make a alert box in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Alert severity<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"error\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  This is a custom alert <span class=\"token keyword\">with</span> a different border style<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Alert<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material change border color of mui alert example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, to change border color of mui alert, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">Alert</code> Component. Define a custom CSS class using the <code class=\"language-text\">createTheme</code> function and change border color of mui alert in reate js. </p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> createTheme<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ThemeProvider <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/styles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Alert <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Alert\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> theme <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">createTheme</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">components</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">MuiAlert</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">styleOverrides</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token literal-property property\">root</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          <span class=\"token literal-property property\">border</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"10px solid blue\"</span> \n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">MyCustomAlert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ThemeProvider theme<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>theme<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Alert severity<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"error\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        This is a custom alert <span class=\"token keyword\">with</span> a different border style<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Alert<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>ThemeProvider<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> MyCustomAlert<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and change border color of mui alert in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/90e3c/border-color.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 15.822784810126581%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRkAAAABXRUJQVlA4IDQAAADQAgCdASoUAAMALplotFoiqCgoCACYSygABc6LdBgAAP71B/osspDR7ScEuvCJVsEuAAAA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, border-color-alert\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, border-color-alert\"\n        src=\"/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/8aab1/border-color.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/81b7c/border-color.webp 158w,\n/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/6ea66/border-color.webp 315w,\n/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/8aab1/border-color.webp 630w,\n/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/a70f5/border-color.webp 945w,\n/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/4ef06/border-color.webp 1260w,\n/static/989ae0b60a940c581d7259d4c91d6857/90e3c/border-color.webp 1360w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program change border color of mui alert in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=distracted-banzai-hkytsy\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to change border color of mui alert in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"June 17, 2023","description":"Example of change border color of mui alert in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to change border radius of mui alert in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-17-how-to-change-border-radius-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to change background color of mui alert in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-17-how-to-change-background-color-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-17-how-to-change-border-color-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-06-17-how-to-change-border-radius-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-06-17-how-to-change-background-color-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/"}},
